<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>The Royal College of Radiologists</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence from </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">The Royal College of Radiologists</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> (PEX 0002)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 9.8pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The Royal College of Radiologists (RCR) has over 9,000 Fellows and members worldwide, representing the specialties of clinical oncology and clinical radiology.   The role of the College is to set and maintain the standards for entry to and practice in these specialties, in addition to leading and supporting practitioners throughout their career.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 9.8pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">This response outlines comments from the RCR relating to public expenditure</span></li><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 9.8pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">This response covers areas where the RCR can offer comment and therefore does not respond to all the areas of inquiry the Committee is pursuing.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 9.8pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Efficient and effective management of patients</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Radiology is a key enabler to more efficient and effective management of patients in the community and the safe and effective management of patients in the emergency care pathway.  Early access to diagnostics particularly radiology can often lead to early treatment and better outcomes, and avoids the patient deteriorating and needing acute admission.  In addition, early exclusion of disease through imaging significantly reduces demands on secondary care.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">However, this is not being achieved effectively across England.  A key reason for this is the under-resourcing of imaging which has been made worse by the Nicholson Challenge.  When service improvement methodology and skill mix is applied, there is evidence of great improvements in efficiencies in radiology services but there needs to be an investment and focus on diagnostics if this is going to be consistently achieved.  The issue is exacerbated by evidence of 9% of unfilled established consultant radiologist posts predominantly due to a lack of trainees.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The development of PACS and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">teleradiology</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> could have a major impact in supporting smaller Trusts to provide quality radiology services but this would need a more structured planning approach with the development of radiology resource networks. There is little evidence of a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">strategic approach by either the providers or commissioners. In fact the use of this important technology is actually being used in a very reactive way to solve the current under resource problems.  This is being carried out in an unstructured way which is not likely to be sustainable.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Earlier diagnosis of cancer</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Earlier diagnosis of cancer will reduce the healthcare burden and improve outcomes by diagnosing and treating cancer earlier. This can be enabled by:</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Promoting cancer screening and raising public awareness of early detection</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Expanding and sustaining imaging services in the early diagnosis of cancer.  Early diagnostic investigations undertaken by clinical radiologists have been shown to be cost effective in directing the patient pathway at an early stage towards the appropriate specialist care.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Provision of effective integrated care to all</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Provision of effective integrated care to all, with proper linking of primary, secondary and community care, ensuring appropriate referral back to GP services for effective post-treatment monitoring and follow up will avoid unnecessary duplication of investigations and treatment and help achieve the necessary efficiency savings.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The radiologist is ideally placed to advise primary care on the correct use of imaging.  The RCR has produced a document entitled</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Quality imaging services for primary care </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">with the Royal College of General Practitioners and the Society and College of Radiographers which can be found at the following link:</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><a href="http://www.rcr.ac.uk/docs/radiology/pdf/BFCR(13)2_quality_final.pdf"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.rcr.ac.uk/docs/radiology/pdf/BFCR(13)2_quality_final.pdf</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">We have also produced imaging referral guidelines </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">iRefer</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">which are available as an </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">online version, an app or a booklet.  More information can be found here: </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><a href="http://www.rcr.ac.uk/content.aspx?PageID=995"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.rcr.ac.uk/content.aspx?PageID=995</span></a></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">These can be used by GPs to aid earlier diagnosis, reducing late complications and saving lives and help with optimal utilisation of resources </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and funding – reducing unnecessary referrals.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">November</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:right"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">2</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>